{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'll just start talking\nabout the 17th century."},{"time":2263,"text":"I hope nobody finds that offensive."},{"time":4000,"text":"I -- you know, when I --\nafter I had invented PCR,"},{"time":7000,"text":"I kind of needed a change."},{"time":9000,"text":"And I moved down to La Jolla\nand learned how to surf."},{"time":12000,"text":"And I started living down there\non the beach for a long time."},{"time":15000,"text":"And when surfers are out waiting"},{"time":17000,"text":"for waves,"},{"time":19000,"text":"you probably wonder, if you've never\nbeen out there, what are they doing?"},{"time":21000,"text":"You know, sometimes there's a 10-,\n15-minute break out there"},{"time":23000,"text":"when you're waiting for a wave to come in."},{"time":25024,"text":"They usually talk about the 17th century."},{"time":28000,"text":"You know, they get a real\nbad rap in the world."},{"time":31000,"text":"People think they're sort of lowbrows."},{"time":35000,"text":"One day, somebody suggested\nI read this book."},{"time":37167,"text":"It was called --"},{"time":39000,"text":"it was called \"The Air Pump,\""},{"time":41000,"text":"or something like \"The\nLeviathan and The Air Pump.\""},{"time":43453,"text":"It was a real weird book\nabout the 17th century."},{"time":46000,"text":"And I realized, the roots"},{"time":48000,"text":"of the way I sort of thought"},{"time":50000,"text":"was just the only natural\nway to think about things."},{"time":53000,"text":"That -- you know, I was born\nthinking about things that way,"},{"time":56000,"text":"and I had always\nbeen like a little scientist guy."},{"time":58000,"text":"And when I went to find out something,"},{"time":60000,"text":"I used scientific methods.\nI wasn't real surprised,"},{"time":62000,"text":"you know, when they first told me how --"},{"time":64000,"text":"how you were supposed to do science,"},{"time":66000,"text":"because I'd already been doing it\nfor fun and whatever."},{"time":70000,"text":"But it didn't -- it never occurred to me"},{"time":73000,"text":"that it had to be invented"},{"time":75000,"text":"and that it had been invented"},{"time":77000,"text":"only 350 years ago."},{"time":79000,"text":"You know, it was --"},{"time":81000,"text":"like it happened in England,\nand Germany, and Italy"},{"time":84000,"text":"sort of all at the same time."},{"time":86000,"text":"And the story of that,"},{"time":88000,"text":"I thought, was really fascinating."},{"time":90000,"text":"So I'm going to talk\na little bit about that,"},{"time":92167,"text":"and what exactly is it\nthat scientists are supposed to do."},{"time":95000,"text":"And it's, it's a kind of --"},{"time":97000,"text":"You know, Charles I got beheaded"},{"time":101000,"text":"somewhere early in the 17th century."},{"time":103000,"text":"And the English set up Cromwell"},{"time":105000,"text":"and a whole bunch\nof Republicans or whatever,"},{"time":107167,"text":"and not the kind of Republicans we had."},{"time":110000,"text":"They changed the government,\nand it didn't work."},{"time":114000,"text":"And"},{"time":117000,"text":"Charles II, the son,"},{"time":121000,"text":"was finally put back\non the throne of England."},{"time":123215,"text":"He was really nervous,\nbecause his dad had been,"},{"time":126000,"text":"you know, beheaded for being\nthe King of England"},{"time":128310,"text":"And he was nervous about the fact"},{"time":131000,"text":"that conversations that got going"},{"time":133000,"text":"in, like, bars and stuff"},{"time":135000,"text":"would turn to --"},{"time":137000,"text":"this is kind of -- it's hard to believe,"},{"time":139000,"text":"but people in the 17th century in England"},{"time":141000,"text":"were starting to talk about, you know,"},{"time":143000,"text":"philosophy and stuff in bars."},{"time":145000,"text":"They didn't have TV screens,"},{"time":147000,"text":"and they didn't have\nany football games to watch."},{"time":149358,"text":"And they would get really pissy,"},{"time":151000,"text":"and all of a sudden people would spill\nout into the street and fight"},{"time":154263,"text":"about issues like whether or not"},{"time":156000,"text":"it was okay if Robert Boyle"},{"time":159000,"text":"made a device called the vacuum pump."},{"time":161000,"text":"Now, Boyle was a friend of Charles II."},{"time":164000,"text":"He was a Christian guy\nduring the weekends,"},{"time":167000,"text":"but during the week he was a scientist."},{"time":170000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":171000,"text":"Which was -- back then it was"},{"time":173000,"text":"sort of, you know, well, you know --"},{"time":176000,"text":"if you made this thing --\nhe made this little device,"},{"time":178548,"text":"like kind of like a bicycle pump"},{"time":181000,"text":"in reverse that could suck\nall the air out of --"},{"time":184000,"text":"you know what a bell jar is?\nOne of these things,"},{"time":186000,"text":"you pick it up, put it\ndown, and it's got a seal,"},{"time":188358,"text":"and you can see inside of it,"},{"time":190000,"text":"so you can see what's going\non inside this thing."},{"time":192000,"text":"But what he was trying to do\nwas to pump all the air out of there,"},{"time":195000,"text":"and see what would happen inside there."},{"time":197000,"text":"I mean, the first -- I think\none of the first experiments he did"},{"time":201000,"text":"was he put a bird in there."},{"time":203000,"text":"And people in the 17th century,"},{"time":206000,"text":"they didn't really understand\nthe same way we do"},{"time":209000,"text":"about you know, this stuff is"},{"time":211000,"text":"a bunch of different kinds of molecules,"},{"time":214000,"text":"and we breathe it\nin for a purpose and all that."},{"time":217000,"text":"I mean, fish don't know much about water,"},{"time":219000,"text":"and people didn't know much about air."},{"time":222000,"text":"But both started exploring it."},{"time":224000,"text":"One thing, he put a bird in there,\nand he pumped all the air out,"},{"time":226000,"text":"and the bird died. So he said, hmm..."},{"time":228000,"text":"He said -- he called\nwhat he'd done as making --"},{"time":231000,"text":"they didn't call it\na vacuum pump at the time."},{"time":233215,"text":"Now you call it a vacuum\npump; he called it a vacuum."},{"time":236000,"text":"Right? And immediately,"},{"time":239000,"text":"he got into trouble with the local clergy"},{"time":241000,"text":"who said, you can't make a vacuum."},{"time":244000,"text":"Ah, uh --"},{"time":246000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":249000,"text":"Aristotle said that nature abhors one."},{"time":251000,"text":"I think it was a poor\ntranslation, probably,"},{"time":253120,"text":"but people relied\non authorities like that."},{"time":256000,"text":"And you know, Boyle says, well, shit."},{"time":259000,"text":"I make them all the time."},{"time":261000,"text":"I mean, whatever\nthat is that kills the bird --"},{"time":264000,"text":"and I'm calling it a vacuum."},{"time":266000,"text":"And the religious people said that"},{"time":269000,"text":"if God wanted you to make --"},{"time":272000,"text":"I mean, God is everywhere,"},{"time":274000,"text":"that was one of their rules,\nis God is everywhere."},{"time":276405,"text":"And a vacuum --\nthere's nothing in a vacuum,"},{"time":278525,"text":"so you've -- God couldn't be in there."},{"time":281000,"text":"So therefore the church said that you\ncan't make a vacuum, you know."},{"time":284263,"text":"And Boyle said, bullshit."},{"time":286000,"text":"I mean, you want to call it Godless,"},{"time":288000,"text":"you know, you call it Godless."},{"time":290000,"text":"But that's not my job. I'm not into that."},{"time":292000,"text":"I do that on the weekend. And like --"},{"time":295000,"text":"what I'm trying to do\nis figure out what happens"},{"time":298000,"text":"when you suck everything\nout of a compartment."},{"time":301000,"text":"And he did all these\ncute little experiments."},{"time":303167,"text":"Like he did one with --\nhe had a little wheel,"},{"time":306000,"text":"like a fan, that was"},{"time":309000,"text":"sort of loosely attached,\nso it could spin by itself."},{"time":312000,"text":"He had another fan opposed to it"},{"time":314000,"text":"that he had like a --"},{"time":316000,"text":"I mean, the way I would have done\nthis would be, like, a rubber band,"},{"time":318000,"text":"and, you know, around a tinker\ntoy kind of fan."},{"time":320263,"text":"I know exactly how he did\nit; I've seen the drawings."},{"time":324000,"text":"It's two fans, one which he could\nturn from outside"},{"time":326000,"text":"after he got the vacuum established,"},{"time":328000,"text":"and he discovered that if he pulled\nall the air out of it,"},{"time":331000,"text":"the one fan would no longer\nturn the other one, right?"},{"time":334000,"text":"Something was missing, you know.\nI mean, these are --"},{"time":337000,"text":"it's kind of weird to think that someone\nhad to do an experiment to show that,"},{"time":339000,"text":"but that was what was going\non at the time."},{"time":343976,"text":"And like, there was big arguments about it"},{"time":346000,"text":"in the -- you know, the gin houses\nand in the coffee shops and stuff."},{"time":350000,"text":"And Charles"},{"time":352000,"text":"started not liking that."},{"time":354000,"text":"Charles II was kind of saying, you\nknow, you should keep that --"},{"time":357000,"text":"let's make a place where\nyou can do this stuff"},{"time":360000,"text":"where people don't get so -- you know,"},{"time":362000,"text":"we don't want the -- we don't want to get\nthe people mad at me again. And so --"},{"time":365000,"text":"because when they started\ntalking about religion"},{"time":368000,"text":"and science and stuff like that,"},{"time":370000,"text":"that's when it had sort of gotten\nhis father in trouble."},{"time":372691,"text":"And so,"},{"time":374000,"text":"Charles said, I'm going\nto put up the money"},{"time":376072,"text":"give you guys a building,"},{"time":378000,"text":"come here and you can\nmeet in the building,"},{"time":380072,"text":"but just don't talk\nabout religion in there."},{"time":382192,"text":"And that was fine with Boyle."},{"time":384000,"text":"He said, OK, we're going\nto start having these meetings."},{"time":386691,"text":"And anybody who wants to do science is --"},{"time":389000,"text":"this is about the time that Isaac\nNewton was starting to whip out"},{"time":391000,"text":"a lot of really interesting things."},{"time":393000,"text":"And there was all kind of people\nthat would come to the Royal Society,"},{"time":396358,"text":"they called it. You had to be\ndressed up pretty well."},{"time":399000,"text":"It wasn't like a TED conference."},{"time":401000,"text":"That was the only criteria,\nwas that you be --"},{"time":403000,"text":"you looked like a gentleman,\nand they'd let anybody could come."},{"time":406024,"text":"You didn't have to be a member then."},{"time":408000,"text":"And so, they would come\nin and you would do --"},{"time":410215,"text":"Anybody that was going\nto show an experiment,"},{"time":413000,"text":"which was kind of a new word at the time,"},{"time":415000,"text":"demonstrate some principle,"},{"time":417000,"text":"they had to do it on stage,\nwhere everybody could see it."},{"time":420000,"text":"So they were --"},{"time":422000,"text":"the really important part of this was,"},{"time":424000,"text":"you were not supposed to talk"},{"time":426000,"text":"about final causes, for instance."},{"time":429000,"text":"And God was out of the picture."},{"time":431000,"text":"The actual nature of reality\nwas not at issue."},{"time":435000,"text":"You're not supposed to talk\nabout the absolute nature of anything."},{"time":438167,"text":"You were not supposed\nto talk about anything"},{"time":440287,"text":"that you couldn't demonstrate."},{"time":442000,"text":"So if somebody could see it, you could\nsay, here's how the machine works,"},{"time":445501,"text":"here's what we do, and then\nhere's what happens."},{"time":449000,"text":"And seeing what happens, it was OK"},{"time":451000,"text":"to generalize,"},{"time":453000,"text":"and say, I'm sure that this\nwill happen anytime"},{"time":456000,"text":"we make one of these things."},{"time":458000,"text":"And so you can start making up some rules."},{"time":460024,"text":"You say, anytime you have a vacuum state,"},{"time":463000,"text":"you will discover that one wheel\nwill not turn another one,"},{"time":466000,"text":"if the only connection between them"},{"time":468000,"text":"is whatever was there before the vacuum.\nThat kind of thing."},{"time":471000,"text":"Candles can't burn in a vacuum,"},{"time":473000,"text":"therefore, probably\nsparklers wouldn't either."},{"time":476000,"text":"It's not clear; actually sparklers will,"},{"time":478000,"text":"but they didn't know that."},{"time":480000,"text":"They didn't have sparklers. But, they --"},{"time":482000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":487000,"text":"-- you can make up rules,\nbut they have to relate"},{"time":490000,"text":"only to the things\nthat you've been able to demonstrate."},{"time":492000,"text":"And most the demonstrations\nhad to do with visuals."},{"time":495000,"text":"Like if you do an experiment on stage,"},{"time":497000,"text":"and nobody can see it, they can just hear it,\nthey would probably think you were freaky."},{"time":500000,"text":"I mean, reality is what you can see."},{"time":503000,"text":"That wasn't an explicit\nrule in the meeting,"},{"time":507000,"text":"but I'm sure that was part of it,\nyou know. If people hear voices,"},{"time":509000,"text":"and they can't see and associate\nit with somebody,"},{"time":512000,"text":"that person's probably not there."},{"time":514000,"text":"But the general idea\nthat you could only --"},{"time":518000,"text":"you could only really talk\nabout things in that place"},{"time":520548,"text":"that had some kind of experimental basis."},{"time":523000,"text":"It didn't matter what Thomas Hobbes,"},{"time":525000,"text":"who was a local philosopher,"},{"time":527000,"text":"said about it, you know,"},{"time":529000,"text":"because you weren't going\nto be talking final causes."},{"time":531548,"text":"What's happening here,"},{"time":533000,"text":"in the middle of the 17th century,"},{"time":535000,"text":"was that what became my field --"},{"time":537000,"text":"science, experimental science --"},{"time":539000,"text":"was pulling itself away,"},{"time":541000,"text":"and it was in a physical way, because we're\ngoing to do it in this room over here,"},{"time":544000,"text":"but it was also what -- it\nwas an amazing thing that happened."},{"time":546000,"text":"Science had been all interlocked"},{"time":548000,"text":"with theology, and philosophy,"},{"time":550000,"text":"and -- and -- and mathematics,"},{"time":553000,"text":"which is really not science."},{"time":556000,"text":"But experimental science had\nbeen tied up with all those things."},{"time":559072,"text":"And the mathematics part"},{"time":562000,"text":"and the experimental science part"},{"time":564000,"text":"was pulling away from philosophy."},{"time":566000,"text":"And -- things --"},{"time":568000,"text":"we never looked back."},{"time":570000,"text":"It's been so cool since then."},{"time":573000,"text":"I mean, it just -- it just -- untangled\na thing that was really impeding"},{"time":578000,"text":"technology from being developed."},{"time":580000,"text":"And, I mean, everybody in this room --"},{"time":582000,"text":"now, this is 350 short years ago."},{"time":584000,"text":"Remember, that's a short time."},{"time":586000,"text":"It was 300,000, probably, years ago"},{"time":589000,"text":"that most of us, the ancestors\nof most of us in this room"},{"time":592000,"text":"came up out of Africa\nand turned to the left."},{"time":595000,"text":"You know, the ones that turned\nto the right, there are some of those"},{"time":597000,"text":"in the Japanese translation."},{"time":599000,"text":"But that happened very -- a long time ago"},{"time":602000,"text":"compared to"},{"time":604000,"text":"350 short years ago."},{"time":606000,"text":"But in that 350 years,"},{"time":608000,"text":"the place has just undergone\na lot of changes."},{"time":611000,"text":"In fact, everybody in this room probably,"},{"time":613000,"text":"especially if you picked up your bag --"},{"time":616000,"text":"some of you, I know, didn't\npick up your bags --"},{"time":618000,"text":"but if you picked up your bag,\neverybody in this room"},{"time":620000,"text":"has got in their pocket,\nor back in their room,"},{"time":622263,"text":"something"},{"time":624000,"text":"that 350 years ago,"},{"time":626000,"text":"kings would have gone to war to have."},{"time":629000,"text":"I mean, if you can think how important --"},{"time":631000,"text":"If you have a GPS system\nand there are no satellites,"},{"time":633000,"text":"it's not going to be much use.\nBut, like --"},{"time":635072,"text":"but, you know, if somebody\nhad a GPS system"},{"time":637144,"text":"in the 17th century"},{"time":640000,"text":"some king would have\ngotten together an army"},{"time":642000,"text":"and gone to get it, you know.\nIf that person --"},{"time":644000,"text":"Audience: For the teddy bear?\nThe teddy bear?"},{"time":646167,"text":"Kary Mullis: They might have done\nit for the teddy bear, yeah."},{"time":649144,"text":"But -- all of us own stuff."},{"time":651000,"text":"I mean, individuals own things"},{"time":653000,"text":"that kings would have\ndefinitely gone to war to get."},{"time":655501,"text":"And this is just 350 years."},{"time":657000,"text":"Not a whole lot of people\ndoing this stuff."},{"time":659072,"text":"You know, the important people --"},{"time":661000,"text":"you can almost read about their lives,"},{"time":663000,"text":"about all the really important\npeople that made advances, you know."},{"time":666215,"text":"And, I mean --"},{"time":668000,"text":"this kind of stuff, you\nknow, all this stuff"},{"time":671000,"text":"came from that separation"},{"time":673000,"text":"of this little sort of thing that we do --"},{"time":676000,"text":"now I, when I was a boy"},{"time":678000,"text":"was born sort of with this idea"},{"time":680000,"text":"that if you want to know something --"},{"time":682000,"text":"you know, maybe it's because my old\nman was gone a lot,"},{"time":684000,"text":"and my mother didn't\nreally know much science,"},{"time":686215,"text":"but I thought if you want\nto know something about stuff,"},{"time":689000,"text":"you do it -- you make\nan experiment, you know."},{"time":691215,"text":"You get -- you get, like --"},{"time":693000,"text":"I just had a natural feeling for science"},{"time":696000,"text":"and setting up experiments. I thought\nthat was the way everybody had always thought."},{"time":698000,"text":"I thought that anybody\nwith any brains will do it that way."},{"time":701000,"text":"It isn't true. I mean,\nthere's a lot of people --"},{"time":704000,"text":"You know, I was one of those\nscientists that was --"},{"time":707000,"text":"got into trouble the other night at dinner"},{"time":709024,"text":"because of the post-modernism thing."},{"time":711000,"text":"And I didn't mean, you know\n-- where is that lady?"},{"time":713000,"text":"Audience: Here."},{"time":714000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":715000,"text":"KM: I mean, I didn't really\nthink of that as an argument"},{"time":717691,"text":"so much as just a lively discussion."},{"time":720000,"text":"I didn't take it personally, but --"},{"time":723000,"text":"I just -- I had -- I naively had thought,"},{"time":726000,"text":"until this surfing experience\nstarted me into the 17th century,"},{"time":729024,"text":"I'd thought that's just\nthe way people thought,"},{"time":731287,"text":"and everybody did,\nand they recognized reality"},{"time":734000,"text":"by what they could see\nor touch or feel or hear."},{"time":737000,"text":"At any rate, when I was a boy,"},{"time":742000,"text":"I, like, for instance, I had this --"},{"time":744000,"text":"I got this little book\nfrom Fort Sill, Oklahoma --"},{"time":746000,"text":"This is about the time\nthat George Dyson's dad"},{"time":748215,"text":"was starting to blow nuclear --"},{"time":750000,"text":"thinking about blowing\nup nuclear rockets and stuff."},{"time":753000,"text":"I was thinking about making\nmy own little rockets."},{"time":756000,"text":"And I knew that frogs -- little frogs --"},{"time":759000,"text":"had aspirations of space travel,"},{"time":761000,"text":"just like people. And I --"},{"time":763000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":766000,"text":"I was looking for a --"},{"time":768000,"text":"a propulsion system"},{"time":770000,"text":"that would like, make a rocket, like,"},{"time":772000,"text":"maybe about four feet high\ngo up a couple of miles."},{"time":774453,"text":"And, I mean, that was my sort of goal."},{"time":777000,"text":"I wanted it to go out of sight and then\nI wanted this little parachute"},{"time":780358,"text":"to come back with the frog in it."},{"time":783000,"text":"And -- I -- I --"},{"time":785000,"text":"I got this book from Fort Sill, Oklahoma,"},{"time":787000,"text":"where there's a missile base."},{"time":789000,"text":"They send it out for amateur rocketeers,"},{"time":792000,"text":"and"},{"time":794000,"text":"it said in there"},{"time":796000,"text":"do not ever heat a mixture\nof potassium perchlorate and sugar."},{"time":799000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":802000,"text":"You know,"},{"time":804000,"text":"that's what you call a lead."},{"time":806000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":808000,"text":"You sort of -- now you say,\nwell, let's see if I can"},{"time":810000,"text":"get hold of some potassium chlorate\nand sugar, perchlorate and sugar,"},{"time":813000,"text":"and heat it; it would be interesting to see\nwhat it is they don't want me to do,"},{"time":816000,"text":"and what it is going to --\nand how is it going to work."},{"time":818596,"text":"And we didn't have --"},{"time":820000,"text":"like, my mother"},{"time":822000,"text":"presided over the back yard"},{"time":825000,"text":"from an upstairs window,"},{"time":827000,"text":"where she would be ironing\nor something like that."},{"time":829000,"text":"And she was usually just\nsort of keeping an eye on,"},{"time":831000,"text":"and if there was any puffs\nof smoke out there,"},{"time":833215,"text":"she'd lean out and admonish us all"},{"time":835000,"text":"not to blow our eyes out. That was her --"},{"time":840000,"text":"You know, that was kind of the worst\nthing that could happen to us."},{"time":842000,"text":"That's why I thought, as long\nas I don't blow my eyes out..."},{"time":844000,"text":"I may not care about the fact"},{"time":847000,"text":"that it's prohibited\nfrom heating this solution."},{"time":849000,"text":"I'm going to do it\ncarefully, but I'll do it."},{"time":851167,"text":"It's like anything else that's prohibited:"},{"time":853191,"text":"you do it behind the garage."},{"time":855000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":857000,"text":"So, I went to the drug store"},{"time":859000,"text":"and I tried to buy\nsome potassium perchlorate"},{"time":862000,"text":"and it wasn't unreasonable then for a kid"},{"time":864000,"text":"to walk into a drug store\nand buy chemicals."},{"time":867000,"text":"Nowadays, it's no ma'am,"},{"time":869000,"text":"check your shoes. And like --"},{"time":871000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":873000,"text":"But then it wasn't -- they didn't\nhave any, but the guy had --"},{"time":875000,"text":"I said, what kind of salts\nof potassium do you have? You know."},{"time":878000,"text":"And he had potassium nitrate."},{"time":880000,"text":"And I said, that might do\nthe same thing, whatever it is."},{"time":883000,"text":"I'm sure it's got to do with rockets\nor it wouldn't be in that manual."},{"time":886000,"text":"And so I -- I did some experiments."},{"time":888000,"text":"You know, I started\noff with little tiny amounts"},{"time":890310,"text":"of potassium nitrate and sugar,"},{"time":892000,"text":"which was readily available,"},{"time":894000,"text":"and I mixed it in different proportions,"},{"time":896000,"text":"and I tried to light it on fire."},{"time":899000,"text":"Just to see what would happen,\nif you mixed it together."},{"time":901691,"text":"And it -- they burned."},{"time":903000,"text":"It burned kind of slow,\nbut it made a nice smell,"},{"time":905000,"text":"compared to other rocket\nfuels I had tried,"},{"time":907072,"text":"that all had sulfur in them."},{"time":909000,"text":"And, it smelt like burnt candy."},{"time":912000,"text":"And then I tried the melting\nbusiness, and I melted it."},{"time":915000,"text":"And then it melted into a little sort\nof syrupy liquid, brown."},{"time":919000,"text":"And then it cooled\ndown to a brick-hard substance,"},{"time":922000,"text":"that when you lit that,"},{"time":924000,"text":"it went off like a bat."},{"time":926000,"text":"I mean, the little bowl of that stuff\nthat had cooled down --"},{"time":928000,"text":"you'd light it, and it would just\nstart dancing around the yard."},{"time":930000,"text":"And I said, there"},{"time":932000,"text":"is a way to get a frog\nup to where he wants to go."},{"time":935000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":936000,"text":"So I started developing --"},{"time":939000,"text":"you know, George's dad had a lot of help.\nI just had my brother."},{"time":942000,"text":"But I -- it took me\nabout -- it took me about,"},{"time":945000,"text":"I'd say, six months"},{"time":947000,"text":"to finally figure\nout all the little things."},{"time":949072,"text":"There's a lot of little things involved"},{"time":951000,"text":"in making a rocket that it\nwill actually work,"},{"time":953215,"text":"even after you have the fuel."},{"time":955000,"text":"But you do it, by -- what I just--"},{"time":957000,"text":"you know, you do experiments,"},{"time":959000,"text":"and you write down things sometimes,"},{"time":960000,"text":"you make observations, you know."},{"time":962000,"text":"And then you slowly build up a theory"},{"time":964000,"text":"of how this stuff works."},{"time":966000,"text":"And it was --\nI was following all the rules."},{"time":968120,"text":"I didn't know what the rules were,"},{"time":970000,"text":"I'm a natural born scientist, I guess,"},{"time":972000,"text":"or some kind of a throwback\nto the 17th century, whatever."},{"time":975000,"text":"But at any rate, we finally did"},{"time":979000,"text":"have a device that would reproduceably"},{"time":981000,"text":"put a frog out of sight"},{"time":983000,"text":"and get him back alive."},{"time":985000,"text":"And we had not --"},{"time":987000,"text":"I mean, we weren't frightened by it."},{"time":990000,"text":"We should have been,\nbecause it made a lot of smoke"},{"time":992453,"text":"and it made a lot of noise,"},{"time":994000,"text":"and it was powerful, you know."},{"time":996000,"text":"And once in a while, they would blow up."},{"time":998000,"text":"But I wasn't worried, by the way,"},{"time":1000000,"text":"about, you know,"},{"time":1002000,"text":"the explosion causing\nthe destruction of the planet."},{"time":1004000,"text":"I hadn't heard about the 10 ways"},{"time":1006000,"text":"that we should be afraid of the --"},{"time":1008000,"text":"By the way,"},{"time":1010000,"text":"I could have thought,"},{"time":1012000,"text":"I'd better not do this because"},{"time":1014000,"text":"they say not to, you know."},{"time":1016000,"text":"And I'd better get permission\nfrom the government."},{"time":1018000,"text":"If I'd have waited around for that,"},{"time":1020000,"text":"I would have never -- the frog\nwould have died, you know."},{"time":1024000,"text":"At any rate, I bring it\nup because it's a good story,"},{"time":1027000,"text":"and he said, tell personal things,\nyou know, and that's a personal --"},{"time":1029000,"text":"I was going to tell you about the first\nnight that I met my wife,"},{"time":1032000,"text":"but that would be too\npersonal, wouldn't it."},{"time":1035000,"text":"So, so I've got something\nelse that's not personal."},{"time":1037453,"text":"But that... process\nis what I think of as science,"},{"time":1040000,"text":"see, where you start with some idea,"},{"time":1043000,"text":"and then instead of, like, looking up,"},{"time":1046000,"text":"every authority that you've ever heard of"},{"time":1048000,"text":"I -- sometimes you do that,"},{"time":1050000,"text":"if you're going to write a paper later,"},{"time":1052000,"text":"you want to figure\nout who else has worked on it."},{"time":1054000,"text":"But in the actual process,\nyou get an idea --"},{"time":1056167,"text":"like, when I got the idea one night"},{"time":1058000,"text":"that I could amplify DNA\nwith two oligonucleotides,"},{"time":1061000,"text":"and I could make lots of copies\nof some little piece of DNA,"},{"time":1064000,"text":"you know, the thinking for that"},{"time":1066000,"text":"was about 20 minutes\nwhile I was driving my car,"},{"time":1070000,"text":"and then instead of going -- I went\nback and I did talk to people about it,"},{"time":1073596,"text":"but if I'd listened to what I heard\nfrom all my friends who were molecular biologists --"},{"time":1078000,"text":"I would have abandoned it."},{"time":1080000,"text":"You know, if I had gone back\nlooking for an authority figure"},{"time":1082000,"text":"who could tell me if it would work or not,"},{"time":1084024,"text":"he would have said, no, it probably won't."},{"time":1086048,"text":"Because the results of it\nwere so spectacular"},{"time":1090000,"text":"that if it worked it was going to change\neverybody's goddamn way of doing molecular biology."},{"time":1093000,"text":"Nobody wants a chemist to come in"},{"time":1095000,"text":"and poke around in their stuff\nlike that and change things."},{"time":1098000,"text":"But if you go to authority,\nand you always don't --"},{"time":1100000,"text":"you don't always get\nthe right answer, see."},{"time":1102072,"text":"But I knew, you'd go into the lab"},{"time":1104000,"text":"and you'd try to make it work yourself.\nAnd then you're the authority,"},{"time":1106000,"text":"and you can say, I know it works,"},{"time":1108000,"text":"because right there in that tube"},{"time":1110000,"text":"is where it happened,"},{"time":1112000,"text":"and here, on this gel,\nthere's a little band there"},{"time":1114000,"text":"that I know that's DNA,\nand that's the DNA I wanted to amplify,"},{"time":1117024,"text":"so there! So it does work."},{"time":1119000,"text":"You know, that's how you do science."},{"time":1121000,"text":"And then you say, well,\nwhat can make it work better?"},{"time":1123000,"text":"And then you figure out better\nand better ways to do it."},{"time":1125000,"text":"But you always work from, from like, facts"},{"time":1127024,"text":"that you have made available to you"},{"time":1130000,"text":"by doing experiments: things\nthat you could do on a stage."},{"time":1132000,"text":"And no tricky shit behind the thing.\nI mean, it's all --"},{"time":1135000,"text":"you've got to be very honest"},{"time":1137000,"text":"with what you're doing if it\nreally is going to work."},{"time":1139000,"text":"I mean, you can't make up results,"},{"time":1141000,"text":"and then do another experiment\nbased on that one."},{"time":1143358,"text":"So you have to be honest."},{"time":1145000,"text":"And I'm basically honest."},{"time":1147000,"text":"I have a fairly bad memory, and dishonesty\nwould always get me in trouble,"},{"time":1150000,"text":"if I, like -- so I've just\nsort of been naturally honest"},{"time":1152691,"text":"and naturally inquisitive,"},{"time":1155000,"text":"and that sort of leads\nto that kind of science."},{"time":1157263,"text":"Now, let's see..."},{"time":1159000,"text":"I've got another five minutes, right?"},{"time":1162000,"text":"OK. All scientists aren't like that."},{"time":1166000,"text":"You know -- and there is a lot --"},{"time":1168000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1170000,"text":"There is a lot -- a lot\nhas been going on since"},{"time":1172263,"text":"Isaac Newton and all that stuff happened."},{"time":1175000,"text":"One of the things that happened\nright around World War II"},{"time":1177000,"text":"in that same time period before,"},{"time":1179000,"text":"and as sure as hell afterwards,"},{"time":1181000,"text":"government got -- realized\nthat scientists aren't strange dudes"},{"time":1184024,"text":"that, you know, hide in ivory towers"},{"time":1187000,"text":"and do ridiculous things with test tube."},{"time":1190000,"text":"Scientists, you know, made World War II"},{"time":1192000,"text":"as we know it quite possible."},{"time":1194000,"text":"They made faster things."},{"time":1197000,"text":"They made bigger guns\nto shoot them down with."},{"time":1200000,"text":"You know, they made drugs\nto give the pilots"},{"time":1203000,"text":"if they were broken up in the process."},{"time":1206000,"text":"They made all kinds of --\nand then finally one giant bomb"},{"time":1209000,"text":"to end the whole thing, right?"},{"time":1211000,"text":"And everybody stepped back\na little and said, you know,"},{"time":1213000,"text":"we ought to invest in this shit,"},{"time":1215000,"text":"because whoever has got\nthe most of these people"},{"time":1218000,"text":"working in the places is going\nto have a dominant position,"},{"time":1221000,"text":"at least in the military, and probably\nin all kind of economic ways."},{"time":1224000,"text":"And they got involved\nin it, and the scientific"},{"time":1226000,"text":"and industrial establishment was born,"},{"time":1228000,"text":"and out of that came a lot of scientists"},{"time":1230000,"text":"who were in there for the money, you know,"},{"time":1233000,"text":"because it was suddenly available."},{"time":1235000,"text":"And they weren't the curious little boys"},{"time":1237000,"text":"that liked to put frogs up in the air."},{"time":1239000,"text":"They were the same people that later\nwent in to medical school, you know,"},{"time":1242000,"text":"because there was money in it, you know. I mean,\nlater, then they all got into business --"},{"time":1245000,"text":"I mean, there are waves of --\ngoing into your high school,"},{"time":1248000,"text":"person saying, you want to be rich, you know,\nbe a scientist. You know, not anymore."},{"time":1251000,"text":"You want to be rich, you be a businessman."},{"time":1253024,"text":"But a lot of people got in it for the money\nand the power and the travel."},{"time":1256525,"text":"That's back when travel was easy."},{"time":1260000,"text":"And those people don't think --"},{"time":1262000,"text":"they don't --"},{"time":1264000,"text":"they don't always tell\nyou the truth, you know."},{"time":1266000,"text":"There is nothing\nin their contract, in fact,"},{"time":1268120,"text":"that makes it to their advantage always,"},{"time":1270120,"text":"to tell you the truth."},{"time":1272000,"text":"And the people I'm talking\nabout are people that like --"},{"time":1275000,"text":"they say that they're\na member of the committee"},{"time":1278000,"text":"called, say, the Inter-Governmental\nPanel on Climate Change."},{"time":1282000,"text":"And they -- and they have these big\nmeetings where they try to figure out"},{"time":1286000,"text":"how we're going to -- how we're\ngoing to continually prove"},{"time":1288786,"text":"that the planet is getting warmer,"},{"time":1291000,"text":"when that's actually contrary\nto most people's sensations."},{"time":1294000,"text":"I mean, if you actually measure"},{"time":1296000,"text":"the temperature over a period --"},{"time":1298000,"text":"I mean, the temperature\nhas been measured now"},{"time":1300167,"text":"pretty carefully for about 50, 60 years --"},{"time":1303000,"text":"longer than that it's been measured,"},{"time":1305000,"text":"but in really nice, precise ways,"},{"time":1307000,"text":"and records have been kept\nfor 50 or 60 years,"},{"time":1310000,"text":"and in fact, the temperature\nhadn't really gone up."},{"time":1312000,"text":"It's like, the average temperature"},{"time":1314000,"text":"has gone up a tiny little bit,"},{"time":1316000,"text":"because the nighttime temperatures"},{"time":1319000,"text":"at the weather stations have\ncome up just a little bit."},{"time":1321000,"text":"But there's a good explanation for that."},{"time":1323000,"text":"And it's that the weather stations\nare all built outside of town,"},{"time":1326120,"text":"where the airport was, and now"},{"time":1328000,"text":"the town's moved out there,\nthere's concrete all around"},{"time":1330000,"text":"and they call it the skyline effect."},{"time":1332000,"text":"And most responsible people"},{"time":1334000,"text":"that measure temperatures realize"},{"time":1336000,"text":"you have to shield\nyour measuring device from that."},{"time":1338453,"text":"And even then, you know,"},{"time":1341000,"text":"because the buildings get\nwarm in the daytime,"},{"time":1342000,"text":"and they keep it a little warmer at night."},{"time":1344024,"text":"So the temperature has\nbeen, sort of, inching up."},{"time":1346024,"text":"It should have been. But not a lot.\nNot like, you know --"},{"time":1349000,"text":"the first guy -- the first\nguy that got the idea"},{"time":1351000,"text":"that we're going to fry ourselves here,"},{"time":1353000,"text":"actually, he didn't think of it that way."},{"time":1355000,"text":"His name was Sven Arrhenius.\nHe was Swedish, and he said,"},{"time":1358000,"text":"if you double the CO2\nlevel in the atmosphere,"},{"time":1361000,"text":"which he thought might\n-- this is in 1900 --"},{"time":1364000,"text":"the temperature ought to go\nup about 5.5 degrees, he calculated."},{"time":1367072,"text":"He was thinking of the earth\nas, kind of like,"},{"time":1369287,"text":"you know, like a completely\ninsulated thing"},{"time":1372000,"text":"with no stuff in it, really,"},{"time":1374000,"text":"just energy coming down, energy leaving."},{"time":1376000,"text":"And so he came up with this theory,"},{"time":1378000,"text":"and he said, this will be cool,"},{"time":1380000,"text":"because it'll be a longer\ngrowing season in Sweden,"},{"time":1383000,"text":"you know, and the surfers liked it,"},{"time":1385000,"text":"the surfers thought, that's a cool idea,"},{"time":1387000,"text":"because it's pretty cold\nin the ocean sometimes, and --"},{"time":1390000,"text":"but a lot of other people later on"},{"time":1392000,"text":"started thinking it\nwould be bad, you know."},{"time":1395000,"text":"But nobody actually\ndemonstrated it, right?"},{"time":1397072,"text":"I mean, the temperature as measured --"},{"time":1399000,"text":"and you can find this\non our wonderful Internet,"},{"time":1401310,"text":"you just go and look\nfor all NASAs records,"},{"time":1404000,"text":"and all the Weather Bureau's records,"},{"time":1406000,"text":"and you'll look at it yourself,\nand you'll see, the temperature has just --"},{"time":1409000,"text":"the nighttime temperature measured\non the surface of the planet"},{"time":1412024,"text":"has gone up a tiny little bit."},{"time":1414000,"text":"So if you just average that and the daytime\ntemperature, it looks like it went up"},{"time":1416000,"text":"about .7 degrees in this century."},{"time":1419000,"text":"But in fact, it was just coming up --"},{"time":1421000,"text":"it was the nighttime; the daytime\ntemperatures didn't go up."},{"time":1423882,"text":"So -- and Arrhenius' theory --"},{"time":1426000,"text":"and all the global warmers think --"},{"time":1428000,"text":"they would say, yeah, it should\ngo up in the daytime, too,"},{"time":1430000,"text":"if it's the greenhouse effect."},{"time":1432000,"text":"Now, people like things\nthat have, like, names like that,"},{"time":1435000,"text":"that they can envision it, right?\nI mean --"},{"time":1438000,"text":"but people don't like things\nlike this, so -- most -- I mean,"},{"time":1440929,"text":"you don't get all excited about things"},{"time":1443000,"text":"like the actual evidence, you know,"},{"time":1445000,"text":"which would be evidence for strengthening"},{"time":1447000,"text":"of the tropical circulation in the 1990s."},{"time":1450000,"text":"It's a paper that came out in February,"},{"time":1452000,"text":"and most of you probably\nhadn't heard about it."},{"time":1455000,"text":"\"Evidence for Large Decadal Variability"},{"time":1457000,"text":"in the Tropical Mean\nRadiative Energy Budget.\""},{"time":1461000,"text":"Excuse me. Those papers\nwere published by NASA,"},{"time":1464000,"text":"and some scientists\nat Columbia, and Viliki"},{"time":1466072,"text":"and a whole bunch of people, Princeton."},{"time":1469000,"text":"And those two papers came\nout in Science Magazine,"},{"time":1472000,"text":"February the first,"},{"time":1474000,"text":"and these -- the conclusion\nin both of these papers,"},{"time":1477000,"text":"and in also the Science editor's, like,"},{"time":1480000,"text":"descriptions of these\npapers, for, you know,"},{"time":1482120,"text":"for the quickie,"},{"time":1484000,"text":"is that our theories about global warming"},{"time":1486000,"text":"are completely wrong. I mean,"},{"time":1488000,"text":"what these guys were doing,"},{"time":1490000,"text":"and this is what -- the NASA people\nhave been saying this for a long time."},{"time":1493000,"text":"They say, if you measure the temperature\nof the atmosphere, it isn't going up --"},{"time":1496000,"text":"it's not going up at all. We've doing\nit very carefully now for 20 years,"},{"time":1499501,"text":"from satellites, and it isn't going up."},{"time":1502000,"text":"And in this paper, they show\nsomething much more striking,"},{"time":1505000,"text":"and that was that they did\nwhat they call a radiation --"},{"time":1508000,"text":"and I'm not going to go into the details\nof it, actually it's quite complicated,"},{"time":1511000,"text":"but it isn't as complicated\nas they might make you think it is"},{"time":1514000,"text":"by the words they use in those papers.\nIf you really get down to it, they say,"},{"time":1517000,"text":"the sun puts out a certain\namount of energy --"},{"time":1519215,"text":"we know how much that is --"},{"time":1521000,"text":"it falls on the earth, the earth\ngives back a certain amount."},{"time":1523929,"text":"When it gets warm it generates --"},{"time":1526000,"text":"it makes redder energy --\nI mean, like infra-red,"},{"time":1529000,"text":"like something that's warm\ngives off infra-red."},{"time":1532000,"text":"The whole business\nof the global warming --"},{"time":1534072,"text":"trash, really,"},{"time":1536000,"text":"is that -- if the -- if there's too\nmuch CO2 in the atmosphere,"},{"time":1539024,"text":"the heat that's trying to escape"},{"time":1541000,"text":"won't be able to get out. But\nthe heat coming from the sun,"},{"time":1544000,"text":"which is mostly down in the --\nit's like 350 nanometers,"},{"time":1547000,"text":"which is where it's centered --\nthat goes right through CO2."},{"time":1550000,"text":"So you still get heated,\nbut you don't dissipate any."},{"time":1552000,"text":"Well, these guys measured\nall of those things."},{"time":1554000,"text":"I mean, you can talk about that stuff,"},{"time":1556000,"text":"and you can write these large reports,\nand you can get government money to do it,"},{"time":1559882,"text":"but these -- they actually measured it,"},{"time":1562000,"text":"and it turns\nout that in the last 10 years --"},{"time":1564167,"text":"that's why they say \"decadal\" there --"},{"time":1566167,"text":"that the energy -- that the level"},{"time":1569000,"text":"of what they call \"imbalance\""},{"time":1571000,"text":"has been way the hell\nover what was expected."},{"time":1574000,"text":"Like, the amount of imbalance --"},{"time":1577000,"text":"meaning, heat's coming\nin and it's not going out"},{"time":1580000,"text":"that you would get\nfrom having double the CO2,"},{"time":1582215,"text":"which we're not anywhere\nnear that, by the way."},{"time":1585000,"text":"But if we did, in 2025 or something,"},{"time":1587000,"text":"have double the CO2 as we had in 1900,"},{"time":1590000,"text":"they say it would be\nincrease the energy budget"},{"time":1592263,"text":"by about -- in other words,"},{"time":1595000,"text":"one watt per square centimeter more"},{"time":1597000,"text":"would be coming in than going out."},{"time":1599000,"text":"So the planet should get warmer."},{"time":1602000,"text":"Well, they found out in this\nstudy -- these two studies"},{"time":1604644,"text":"by two different teams --"},{"time":1606000,"text":"that five and a half watts"},{"time":1608000,"text":"per square meter"},{"time":1610000,"text":"had been coming in from 1998, 1999,"},{"time":1613000,"text":"and the place didn't get warmer."},{"time":1615000,"text":"So the theory's kaput -- it's nothing."},{"time":1617000,"text":"These papers should have been called,"},{"time":1619000,"text":"\"The End to the Global\nWarming Fiasco,\" you know."},{"time":1622000,"text":"They're concerned,"},{"time":1624000,"text":"and you can tell they have very\nguarded conclusions in these papers,"},{"time":1627000,"text":"because they're talking\nabout big laboratories"},{"time":1629215,"text":"that are funded by lots of money"},{"time":1631000,"text":"and by scared people."},{"time":1633000,"text":"You know, if they said, you know what?"},{"time":1635000,"text":"There isn't a problem\nwith global warming any longer,"},{"time":1637000,"text":"so we can -- you know, they're funding."},{"time":1639000,"text":"And if you start a grant request\nwith something like that,"},{"time":1642000,"text":"and say, global warming\nobviously hadn't happened..."},{"time":1644453,"text":"if they -- if they -- if they actually\n-- if they actually said that,"},{"time":1646453,"text":"I'm getting out."},{"time":1648000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1651000,"text":"I'll stand up too, and --"},{"time":1653000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1655000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1658000,"text":"They have to say that."},{"time":1660000,"text":"They had to be very cautious."},{"time":1662000,"text":"But what I'm saying is,\nyou can be delighted,"},{"time":1664167,"text":"because the editor\nof Science, who is no dummy,"},{"time":1667000,"text":"and both of these fairly professional --"},{"time":1670000,"text":"really professional teams, have\nreally come to the same conclusion"},{"time":1673000,"text":"and in the bottom lines in their papers"},{"time":1675000,"text":"they have to say, what this means\nis, that what we've been thinking,"},{"time":1678000,"text":"was the global circulation\nmodel that we predict"},{"time":1680263,"text":"that the earth is going to get overheated"},{"time":1682263,"text":"that it's all wrong.\nIt's wrong by a large factor."},{"time":1685000,"text":"It's not by a small one. They just --"},{"time":1688000,"text":"they just misinterpreted\nthe fact that the earth --"},{"time":1691000,"text":"there's obviously some mechanisms going on"},{"time":1693024,"text":"that nobody knew about,"},{"time":1695000,"text":"because the heat's coming\nin and it isn't getting warmer."},{"time":1697000,"text":"So the planet is a pretty\namazing thing, you know,"},{"time":1700000,"text":"it's big and horrible --\nand big and wonderful,"},{"time":1702000,"text":"and it does all kinds of things\nwe don't know anything about."},{"time":1705000,"text":"So I mean, the reason I put\nthose things all together,"},{"time":1707000,"text":"OK, here's the way you're\nsupposed to do science --"},{"time":1709000,"text":"some science is done for other\nreasons, and just curiosity."},{"time":1712000,"text":"And there's a lot of things\nlike global warming,"},{"time":1714310,"text":"and ozone hole and you know,"},{"time":1716000,"text":"a whole bunch of scientific public issues,"},{"time":1718024,"text":"that if you're interested in them,"},{"time":1720000,"text":"then you have to get down the details,\nand read the papers called,"},{"time":1723120,"text":"\"Large Decadal Variability in the...\""},{"time":1725000,"text":"You have to figure\nout what all those words mean."},{"time":1727310,"text":"And if you just listen to the guys"},{"time":1729000,"text":"who are hyping those issues,\nand making a lot of money out of it,"},{"time":1732000,"text":"you'll be misinformed, and you'll be\nworrying about the wrong things."},{"time":1735310,"text":"Remember the 10 things that are going\nto get you. The -- one of them --"},{"time":1738715,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1740000,"text":"And the asteroids is the one I really\nagree with there."},{"time":1743000,"text":"I mean, you've got to watch out for asteroids.\nOK, thank you for having me here."},{"time":1746834,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}